a minimum distance of characteristic points on the first contour of the character;
a maximum distance of characteristic points on the second contour of the character;
a width of the character; and
a height of the character.

12. The device of claim 8,
wherein performing the lateral view analysis on the character data of the two or more component characters includes locating characteristic points on the first and second contours of first and second component characters of the two or more component characters, including dividing each of the first and second component characters into segments, wherein a characteristic point is located in each segment on the first contour and the second contour of each of the first and second component characters;
wherein the computing device is further configured to generate a feature vector of each of the first and second component characters based on the lateral view analysis;
wherein identifying the first and second component characters is based on the feature vector of each of the first and second component characters, respectively; and
wherein each of the feature vectors comprises:
a minimum distance of characteristic points on the first contour of the component character corresponding to the feature vector;
a maximum distance of characteristic points on the second contour of the corresponding component character;
a width of the corresponding component character; and
a height of the corresponding component character.

16. The method of claim 15, wherein the one or more characters have a first contour and a second contour;
wherein performing lateral analysis further comprises locating characteristic points on the first and second contours; and
wherein a characteristic point is located in each segment on the first contour and the second contour.

17. The method of claim 15,
wherein the one or more characters have a first contour and a second contour;
wherein performing lateral analysis further comprises locating characteristic points on the first and second contours, wherein a characteristic point is located in each segment on the first contour and the second contour;
wherein the segments and the characteristic points are equal in number; and
wherein a number of characteristic points at relatively lower portions of the one or more characters is greater than a number of characteristic points at relatively higher portions of the one or more characters.

20. The method of claim 15,
wherein the one or more characters have a first contour and a second contour;
